
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `column` baraye moratab kardan voroodi (input) be shekl-e sotooni (columns) be kar miravad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta data-ha ra be shekl-e ghabl-khani va ba tartib namayesh dahid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `column -s [jodakonandeh] -t` --> 🗂️ Joda kardan data ba yek character khas va moratab kardan an be shekl jadvali. (`-s` baraye moshakhas kardane jodakonandeh (separator) va `-t` baraye jadval-bandi (table formatting) ast.)
    🔹 `column -x` --> ↔️ Por kardane sotoon-ha az chap be rast (horizontally) avazhe por kardane amoodi (vertically) ke halate pishfarz ast.
    🔹 `column -n` --> 🔢 Hesab nakardan sotoon-haye khali.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ echo "name:Ali,age:30,city:Tehran" | column -s , -t

    🔹 Moratab kardane string ba estefade az `,` be عنوانه jodakonandeh.

    $ cat data.txt | column -t

    🔹 Moratab kardane content file `data.txt` be shekl jadvali.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ echo "a b c d e f" | column -x -t

    🔹  In dastoor horizantaly data ro moratab mikone va natije ro be soorate sotooni namayesh mide.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `column` command is used to format input into columns. It helps you display data in a readable and organized way.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `column -s [separator] -t` --> 🗂️ Separate data using a specific character and format it into a table. (`-s` is used to specify the separator, and `-t` enables table formatting.)
    🔹 `column -x` --> ↔️ Fill columns horizontally instead of the default vertical filling.
    🔹 `column -n` --> 🔢 Ignore empty columns.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ echo "name:Ali,age:30,city:Tehran" | column -s , -t

    🔹 Format the string using `,` as a separator.

    $ cat data.txt | column -t

    🔹 Format the content of `data.txt` into a table.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ echo "a b c d e f" | column -x -t

    🔹 This command formats the data horizontally and displays the result in columns.
